  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "The Colombo Plan for Cooperative Economic and Social Development in Asia and the Pacific (The Colombo Plan) is a regional inter-governmental organisation established to enhance economic and social development in the region. Australian assistance is provided through: core budget support; and a contribution to the Colombo Plan Drug Advisory Program (DAP). The total value of this initiative is $0.2 million over four years, starting 2009-10.\r\n\r\n\tPARTNER : Colombo Plan Council (Secretariat)"
